# Background Async Job Queue & Polling

The goal is to implement MVP background job processing in the FastAPI backend without external dependencies like Redis or Celery, using a robust Python `ThreadPoolExecutor`. The frontend will poll the API for updates.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Components

#### [NEW] `app/services/job_queue.py`
- Create a global `ThreadPoolExecutor` (max 4 workers).
- Define `enqueue_analysis(analysis_id, user_id)`:
  - Submits `run_full_analysis` to the thread pool wrapper dynamically.
  - Wraps the execution with a `try/except` block to guarantee any unhandled exceptions are caught and explicitly mark the [analyses](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/routers/analyses.py#180-206) DB record status as `failed` with the `error_reason`.

#### [MODIFY] [app/main.py](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/main.py)
- Import `get_executor` and `shutdown_executor`.
- Update the FastAPI [lifespan](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/main.py#31-42) manager to start the executor on startup and cleanly shut it down (`wait=True`) during shutdown, ensuring no jobs randomly die mid-flight when the server stops.

#### [MODIFY] [app/services/analysis_service.py](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/services/analysis_service.py)
- Rename [trigger_analysis_job](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/services/analysis_service.py#24-140) to `run_full_analysis`.
- Ensure the very first asyncpg DB write correctly moves the status to `processing`. (Already implemented, will just verify the name change and signature propagation).

#### [MODIFY] [app/models/schemas.py](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/models/schemas.py)
- Add `AnalysisStatusResponse(BaseModel)` to formally type-check the new GET status polling endpoint payload (`analysis_id`, `status`, `error_reason`).

#### [MODIFY] [app/routers/analyses.py](file:///f:/C%20drive%20data/squintscale/backend/app/routers/analyses.py)
- Remove FastAPI `BackgroundTasks` injections.
- In `POST /upload` and `POST /url`, directly invoke `enqueue_analysis(analysis_id, user_id)` after the record is created.
- Add an entirely new endpoint `GET /{analysis_id}/status` that performs an ultra-fast query on the DB just to fetch the `status` and `error_reason` strings to satisfy the frontend poller.

